AlarmProfile.Description: "The AMF service is not able to provide its service for one of several reasons. The 'SafAISProbableCause' explains why AMF is unable to provide service"

"This trap notifies the system administrator that AMF was unable to successfully instantiate the component 'saAmfCompName'. The specific mechanism used to instantiate a component will vary based on component category."

"This trap notifies the system administrator that AMF was unable to successfully cleanup the component 'saAmfCompName'. The specific mechanism used to cleanup a component will vary based on component category."
"A component designated by 'saAmfCompName' failed and a cluster reset recovery as recommended by the component is being done."

"A particular work assignment indicated by the 'saAmfSIName' is no longer assigned to a SU and is potentially causing a service disruption. This alarm is typically generated when AMF was unable to successfully execute recovery policies in case of a failure (Node/SU etc.) inorder to prevent the service disruption and maintain service availability. In this scenario the assignment state of the SI transitions to UNASSIGNED."

"This alarm is generated by the Availability Management Framework when it reliably confirms the fact that a component that was being proxied previously is no longer proxied, i.e., the Availability Management Framework has not been able to engage another component to assume the mediation responsibility for a component whose designated proxy component has failed."
"Generated when the administrative state of the cluster changes. This Notification contains the current administrative state of the cluster designated by 'saAmfClusterAdminState'."

"Generated when the administrative state of an Application 'saAmfApplicationName' changes. This Notification also contains the current administrative state of the Application designated by 'saAmfApplicationAdminState'."
"Generated when the administrative state of a Node 'saAmfNodeName' changes. This Notification also contains the current administrative state of the Node designated by 'saAmfNodeAdminState'."
"Generated when the administrative state of a SG 'saAmfSGName' changes. This Notification also contains the current administrative state of the SG designated by 'saAmfSGAdminState'"
"Generated when the administrative state of a SU 'saAmfSUName' changes. This Notification also contains the current administrative state of the SU designated by 'saAmfSUAdminState'"
"Generated when the administrative state of a SI 'saAmfSIName' changes. This Notification also contains the current administrative state of the SI designated by 'saAmfSIAdminState'"
"Generated when the operational state of a Node 'saAmfNodeName' changes.This Notification also contains the current operational state of the Node designated by 'saAmfNodeOperationalState'"
"Generated when the operational state of a SU 'saAmfSUName' changes.This Notification also contains the current operational state of the SU designated by 'saAmfSUOperState'"

"Generated when the presence state of a SU 'saAmfSUName' changes to Instantiated, Uninstantiated or Restarting. This Notification also contains the current presence state of the SU designated by 'saAmfSUPresenceState'."

"Produced when the HA state of a SU 'saAmfSUSISuName' changes for a particular SI 'saAmfSUSISiName' assigned to the SU. This Notification also contains the current HA state of the SU designated by 'saAmfSUSIHAState' for the SI in question. This notification should also be produced when a SI is assigned to a service unit for the very first time"

"Generated when the assignment state of a SI 'saAmfSIName' changes except for the transition to UNASSIGNED state. This Notification also contains the current assignment state of the SI designated by 'saAmfSIAssignmentState'"
"The status of a previously unproxied component (saAmfCompName) became proxied, potentially because a proxy component assumed the task of proxying an unproxied component."
